<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<ecoSpold xmlns="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02 ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02.xsd http://www.EcoInvent.org/UsedUserMasterData ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02UserMasterData.xsd">
  <childActivityDataset>
    <activityDescription>
      <activity specialActivityType="0" id="fe4b7299-e5fa-5c89-9cc3-bf5a26628601" activityNameId="c0253141-ffc2-4280-84b0-cd3291ba0dd6" parentActivityId="808cd947-591c-5b46-a739-1ca24285ed49" inheritanceDepth="-1" type="1">
        <activityName xml:lang="en">natural gas, high pressure, domestic supply with seasonal storage</activityName>
        <includedActivitiesStart xml:lang="en">The activity starts from the outbound gate of the natural gas production plants.</includedActivitiesStart>
        <includedActivitiesEnd xml:lang="en">This dataset covers the gas losses and emissions during seasonal storage of domestic supply. The dataset “Natural gas, burned in gas turbine” is used to account for the emissions and infrastructure of the operational energy requirements of the storage capacities. The infrastructure of the storage is neglected in this study as it is assumed to be insignificant. Long-distance pipeline transport from the place of production to the regional distribution networks is not considered. The activity ends at the "entry gate" of national markets for natural gas at high pressure.</includedActivitiesEnd>
        <generalComment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This dataset represents the supply of natural gas [m3], including energy requirements and losses+emissions from seasonal storage, from domestic production in Turkey (Türkiye). The inventory is an extrapolation based on the information provided for other geographies (for which both indigenous production and consumption of natural gas was modelled) in Bussa et al. (2023).</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1">Reference(s):</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="2">Bussa, M., N. Jungbluth, Ch. Meili (2023) Life cycle inventories for long-distance transport and distribution of natural gas. ESU-services Ltd. Schaffhausen, Switzerland. Available from: http://esu-services.ch/data/public-lci-reports/</text>
        </generalComment>
      </activity>
      <classification classificationId="5020424a-5b73-4722-8000-ac205dbd592d">
        <classificationSystem xml:lang="en">ISIC rev.4 ecoinvent</classificationSystem>
        <classificationValue xml:lang="en">3520:Manufacture of gas; distribution of gaseous fuels through mains</classificationValue>
      </classification>
      <geography geographyId="1347b0a0-7d7e-11de-9ae2-0019e336be3a">
        <shortname xml:lang="en">TR</shortname>
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">Turkey</text>
        </comment>
      </geography>
      <technology technologyLevel="3">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">An average leakage rate of 0.1% of the gas stored was used by Bussa et al. (2023), based on previous studies. Furthermore, Bussa et al. assumed that 15% of total natural gas supply is temporarily stored, based on European Commission (2015), for all geographies covered.</text>
        </comment>
      </technology>
      <timePeriod startDate="2021-01-01" endDate="2023-12-31" isDataValidForEntirePeriod="true">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">Transport modes investigated for 2021.</text>
        </comment>
      </timePeriod>
      <macroEconomicScenario macroEconomicScenarioId="d9f57f0a-a01f-42eb-a57b-8f18d6635801">
        <name xml:lang="en">Business-as-Usual</name>
      </macroEconomicScenario>
    </activityDescription>
